+## Canonical GitHub Prompt Version Preflight
+
+At the start of every run, the agent must verify the canonical prompt version from GitHub before executing the remaining runtime phases.
+
+Rules:
+- GitHub is the canonical source of truth for prompt freshness.
+- if the agent name contains `Manager`, compare the in-agent prompt version against `SportManager/SportPrompt.txt`
+- if the agent name contains `Catalog`, compare the in-agent prompt version against `CommonCatalog/CommonPrompt.txt`
+- version comparison must happen before provider discovery, writes, scheduler updates, or report generation
+- if the GitHub PromptVersion differs from the version currently loaded in the agent, the agent must refresh or update itself from the canonical GitHub prompt before continuing
+- if the GitHub PromptVersion matches the in-agent version, the agent may continue the run normally
+- the agent must report whether prompt refresh was `required`, `performed`, `not_required`, or `blocked`
+- if GitHub version verification is unavailable, the agent must report `prompt_version_verification_unavailable`
+- the agent must not claim prompt freshness, canonical identity alignment, or full governed readiness without a successful GitHub version check
+- prompt refresh must preserve existing governed detail and must not downgrade PromptVersion
 
